ZSH, VIM and other configuration files, user specific configuration files,
utilities functions and theme for my personal use.

Each .zshrc-{username} contains specific user information. Yous should just 
copy or create the following symlinks:
ln -s .zshrc-trasher ~/.zshrc-${whoami}
ln -s .zshrc ~/
ln -s .zsh_functions ~/

To use VIM config files, you'll have to create the following symlinks:
ln -s .vim ~/.vim
ln -s .vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s .vimrc.local ~/.vimrc.local
ln -s .vimrc.plugins ~/.vimrc.plugins
ln -s .vimrc.plugins.local ~/.vimrc.plugins.local

Other config files may be linked as well, depending on requirements
